The paper discusses numerical stability and accuracy of fast matrix multiplication algorithms, which are primarily used in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses algorithmic techniques for improving error guarantees, which falls under the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper compares the properties among the class of known practical fast algorithms, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper includes empirical results that test the various improvement techniques, which could fall under cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
